Topics cover > introduction to Bayesian modelling, > examples of Bayesian inference, > arguments for and controversies with Bayesian methods, > actions to be more Bayesian
Vill du ha med namnen finns de här: Johan Lindström, Yf Jiang, Yann Clough, Dragi Anevski, Rasmus Bååth, Krzysztof Podgorski, Ullrika Sahlin, Martin Stjernman
A half day conference bringing together researchers working with or interested in Bayesian methods.
For more information and to register (for free) visit http://www.lucs.lu.se/bayes-at-lund-2015/

flowRoot.flowPara: Johan Lindström, Yf Jiang, Yann Clough, Dragi Anevski, Rasmus Bååth, Krzysztof Podgorski, Ullrika Sahlin and Martin Stjernman
Keynote speaker is Mathias Villani from Linköping University who is presenting Bayesian model inference - why, what and how?
The contributed talks range from Bayes from a frequentist point of view to Bayesian estimation of the local moose population.
